library(stringr)
#player_advanced = read.csv("data/NBA-dataset-stats-player-team-main/player/player_stats_advanced_rs.csv") 
defense = read.csv("~/proj-02-giving-leopard/data/NBA-dataset-stats-player-team-main/player/player_stats_defense_rs.csv")
#player_scoring = read.csv("data/NBA-dataset-stats-player-team-main/player/player_stats_scoring_rs.csv") 
usage = read.csv("~/proj-02-giving-leopard/data/NBA-dataset-stats-player-team-main/player/player_stats_usage_rs.csv") 
salary <- read_csv("~/proj-02-giving-leopard/data/NBA-dataset-stats-player-team-main/salary/player_salary.csv")

# Standardize the Names
# Convert salary$season from '1985-1986' to '1985-86'
salary <- salary %>%
  mutate(
    season_clean = str_replace(season, 
                              "^(\\d{4})-(\\d{4})$", 
                              function(x) {
                                parts <- str_split(x, "-", simplify = TRUE)
                                paste0(parts[1], "-", str_sub(parts[2], 3, 4))
                              }),
    name_clean = str_trim(str_to_upper(name))
  )
usage <- usage %>%
  mutate(PLAYER_NAME = str_to_upper(PLAYER_NAME))

# Clean salary
salary <- salary %>%
  mutate(salary_num = parse_number(salary))

# Join usage and salary
usage_salary <- usage %>%
  mutate(PLAYER_NAME_CLEAN = str_trim(str_to_upper(PLAYER_NAME))) %>%
  left_join(
    salary %>% select(name_clean, season_clean, salary),
    by = c("PLAYER_NAME_CLEAN" = "name_clean", "SEASON" = "season_clean")
  ) %>%
  mutate(salary_num = readr::parse_number(salary))
Warning in left_join(., salary %>% select(name_clean, season_clean, salary), : Detected an unexpected many-to-many relationship between `x` and `y`.
ℹ Row 52 of `x` matches multiple rows in `y`.
ℹ Row 1143 of `y` matches multiple rows in `x`.

  "many-to-many"` to silence this warning.
# Join defense to usage+salary
all_data <- usage_salary %>%
  left_join(defense %>% select(PLAYER_NAME, SEASON, DEF_RATING, DEF_WS), 
            by = c("PLAYER_NAME", "SEASON"))
p1 <- ggplot(all_data, aes(x = PCT_STL, y = salary_num, 
                           color = MIN, text = paste("Player:", PLAYER_NAME, "<br>Season:", SEASON))) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::dollar_format()) +
  labs(x = "Pct Steals (Hustle)", y = "Salary (USD)", color = "Minutes Played",
       title = "Hustle Stat (Pct Steals) vs Salary") +
  theme_minimal()
ggplotly(p1, tooltip = "text")
p2 <- ggplot(all_data, aes(x = PCT_STL, y = MIN, 
                           color = salary_num, text = paste("Player:", PLAYER_NAME))) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.7) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(labels = scales::dollar_format()) +
  labs(x = "Pct Steals (Hustle)", y = "Minutes Played", color = "Salary",
       title = "Hustle Stat vs Minutes Played") +
  theme_minimal()
ggplotly(p2, tooltip = "text")
all_data <- all_data %>%
  mutate(hustle_quartile = ntile(PCT_STL, 4))

p3 <- ggplot(all_data, aes(x = factor(hustle_quartile), y = MIN)) +
  geom_boxplot(fill = "lightblue") +
  labs(x = "Hustle Quartile (Pct Steals)", y = "Minutes Played",
       title = "Minutes Played by Hustle Quartile")
ggplotly(p3)
